  "text": "AddressSanitizer (ASan) is implemented across both LLVM and GCC with the following key files:\n\n**LLVM (sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d):**\n\n1. `compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_interceptors.cpp` — Implements ASan interceptors for standard library functions (libc). It intercepts functions like memcpy, memmove, memset, strlen, strcpy, strcat, pthread_create, etc. in the `__asan` namespace. The primary entry point is `InitializeAsanInterceptors()`.\n\n2. `compiler-rt/lib/asan/asan_rtl.cpp` — The main ASan runtime library file. It implements ASan runtime initialization via `AsanInitInternal()` (static internal function) and the public `__asan_init()` symbol. This is the 'main file of the ASan run-time library'.\n\n3. `llvm/lib/Transforms/Instrumentation/AddressSanitizer.cpp` — The LLVM IR-level instrumentation pass. Contains the `AddressSanitizer` struct (function-level pass) and `ModuleAddressSanitizer` class (module-level pass), plus `AddressSanitizerPass` which is the new pass manager interface that inserts shadow memory checks before every memory access.\n\n**GCC (sg-evals/gcc--96dfb333):**\n\n4. `gcc/asan.cc` — The GCC ASan instrumentation module. Implements ASan instrumentation as a GCC tree/gimple pass. The primary function is `asan_instrument()` which drives the instrumentation, along with `asan_instrument_reads()` and `asan_instrument_writes()` for controlling what gets instrumented.\n\n5. `gcc/asan.h` — The header file declaring GCC's ASan interface. Declares key functions including `asan_function_start()`, `asan_finish_file()`, `asan_emit_stack_protection()`, `asan_protect_global()`, `initialize_sanitizer_builtins()`, and `asan_expand_check_ifn()` among others."
}

